title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.3 - SOCIAL PROTECTION

description.narrative: 1.3 By 2021, social protection policymakers and practitioners are equipped with knowledge, guidance, tools and mechanisms to effectively implement the reformed social protection policy (combining cash assistance with decentralized care services)., which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Adolescent Empowerment (Covid), Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children (Covid), Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance, Public Finance And Local Governance, Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid), Social Protection And Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Strengthened Governance for Equity and Social Inclusion Outcome Result:By 2021, children in situations of particular vulnerability enjoy equitable access to quality health, education and social protection services supported by effective governance mechanisms.

description.narrative: During 2021, UNICEF continued to advocate and provide advice and solutions for a child sensitive social protection system, building the foundations for future work on national discussions on social protection floors. Efforts continued to provide evidence on policy design, so as develop tools and capacities for social protection delivery at local level integrating cash and care, including tools for working in COVID19 and other emergencies. 2021 also marked an important milestone as national consensus was built on regular reporting of multidimensional child poverty. | Status:Met | As-of Date:24/01/2022
